Cardiology testing refers to the various medical procedures and diagnostic tests performed to
assess the health and function of the heart and blood vessels. These tests are essential in
diagnosing and managing a wide range of cardiovascular conditions and diseases. Cardiologists,
who are specialized doctors in heart health, use these tests to evaluate the structure and
function of the heart, identify any abnormalities, and determine appropriate treatment plans.

